         <abstract>
            <p>Cloudy coffee, turbid tea, spots on glassware, and scummy soap residue are visible by-products of hard water used for cooking or cleaning. As an alternative to ion exchange softening, polyphosphate chemicals are often overlooked as a way to control calcium (Ca) and magnesium (Mg) carbonate hardness.</p>
